section.section:
"Unpaid work-based learning experience" means a program that provides a student with structured employer-supervised learning that:
Occurs in the workplace;
Links with classroom instruction;
Is coordinated by a county board or private noncollegiate institution; and
Is conducted in accordance with the terms of an individual written work-based learning agreement between the county board of education or private noncollegiate institution placing a participating student and the employer of that participating student.
